{{Infobox person | name = Laura Eldridge | image = Laura Eldridge by Jeremy Weinberg.jpg | alt = Laura Eldridge, by Jeremy Weinberg | caption = Laura Eldridge, by Jeremy Weinberg | birth_date = <!-- {{Birth date|1965|11|18}} --> | education = | alma_mater = [[Barnard College]] | occupation = Writer, activist | years_active = 2007–current | employer = | website = <!--{{URL|}} --> | footnotes = }}
'''Laura Eldridge''' is a women's health writer and activist. She began working with the legendary women's health activist and author of ''The Doctor's Case Against The Pill'', [[Barbara Seaman]], when studying at [[Barnard College]]. She is co-author of ''The No-Nonsense Guide To Menopause''<ref>Reproductive Writes: Keep Talking: An Interview with Laura Eldridge, Bitch Magazine, April 2, 2010. [http://bitchmagazine.org/post/reproductive-writes-keep-talking-an-interview-with-laura-eldridge]</ref> as well as the co-editor, also with Barbara Seaman, of ''Voices of the Women's Health Movement'' ([[Seven Stories Press]], 2012) a collection of essays, interviews, and commentary by leading activists, writers, doctors, and sociologists on topics ranging across reproductive rights, sex and orgasm, activism, motherhood and birth control.<ref>[http://www.sevenstories.com/book/?GCOI=58322100732420 Seven Stories Press, January 2012]</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Bader|first=Eleanor J.|title=Women Have Been Fighting Misinformation and Oppression of Their Bodies for Decades|url=http://www.alternet.org/story/154603/women_have_been_fighting_misinformation_and_oppression_of_their_bodies_for_decades|publisher=AlterNet|accessdate=22 December 2013}}</ref> She is also the author of ''In Our Control: The Complete Guide to Contraceptive Choices for Women''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kissling|first=Elizabeth|title=Book Review: In Our (Birth) Control|url=http://msmagazine.com/blog/2010/05/20/book-review-in-our-birth-control/|publisher=Ms. Magazine|accessdate=22 December 2013|date=May 20, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Pearson|first=Cynthia|title=Book Review: In Our Control: The Complete Guide to Contraceptive Choices for Women|url=Book Review: In Our Control: The Complete Guide to Contraceptive Choices for Women|publisher=National Women's Health Network|accessdate=22 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=In Our Control: The Complete Guide to Contraceptive Choices for Women|url=http://www.publi